The program was built in MAC OS. I was able to makefile by running command:
gcc -Wall -Wno-deprecated-declarations -o final final.c -framework GLUT -framework OpenGL


I am really proud of how this project turned out. I put many hours into researching, programming and executing this project. Creating this scene took me approximately 40+ hours to do.
That being said these are my major points of recognition I would like you take a closer look on:
- creating the windows primitively on the apartment buildings.
- The engine of the space ship was made by playing around with the values of the curved cylinder function to create this star like shape to it. 
- having the space cars and space ship moving over time. (tried to have them be as irregular as possible within the scope of time of the project).
- texturing the cylinder skyscrapers

FIRST PRESS 0
(JUMP)FIRST PERSON MODE (Jump to certain parts of terrain)
	keys: 1, 2, 3
(JUMP) PERSPECTIVE MODE
	keys: 1, 2, 3

Key binding
  i          Toggle axes
  0          Reset view angle
  ESC        Exit

** first person **
  f          Access first person view
  w/W          move camera forward
  a/A          move camera left
  s/S          move camera  down
  d/D          move camera right
  arrows     look up, down, left, right

**orthogonal and perspective **
  m          Toggle between perspective and orthogonal
  +/-        Changes field of view for perspective
  arrows     Change view angle
  j/J        decrease/increase diffuse
  []         Lower/rise light
  l          Toggles lighting




